result.execSummary: Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Spencer Wyatt Minesal in court with attorney Haley E Wentz.  Defendant Spencer Wyatt Minesal in custody.  Nate Kristian McClure appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviewed doctor's report on the record with the parties.  Parties have no challenges to the report.  Court held colloquy with defendant who informed the court that he is in agreement of the report finding that he is not competent and will not likely regain competency.  On motion of the state, court ordered the case dismissed without prejudice and court ordered the case administratively closed.
Doctor's Report Return on August 5, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Forensic evaluation ordered.  INITIAL APPEARANCE NOT HELD.  Trial court to address INITIAL APPEARANCE.

Defendant Spencer Wyatt Minesal in court with attorney Mary Garvin Guimont.  Defendant Spencer Wyatt Minesal in custody.  Gregg Herman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Spencer Wyatt Minesal appeared by video means with Attorney.  Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.  All parties are advised effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to a Branch of RESERVE JUDGES, Branch 13, Room 508 Courthouse.   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for August 5, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Order for Competency Examination, signed and filed.
